19 Jan 2020 00:10






I want so badly to love Secure, Contain, Baccano! without reservations, because it's undeniably fantastic, schlocky, comic-book fun. I dunno if the 'mystery' theme works so well out of universe given the article plays its hand in that regard relatively early? But Mann's still in the dark throughout, so the process of his investigation and getting to the bottom of this mystery is fair-game.

What is there to say about this article that everyone upthread already hasn't? This is easily the most I've grinned reading any of the articles in the contest so far, and it answers the fundamental question that underpins every existential wondering man has ever had: namely, what if A Good Day to Die Hard didn't make me embarrassed to share a nation with Jai Courtney?

But at the same time, I don't know if my conscience will let me support this as an SCP. The actual SCP part of the file is basically an afterthought because it's not important to the Mannsploitation film that's unfolding. That's a good decision, structure-wise, but it's also one that makes me wonder what even qualifies this as an SCP in the first place, or at least what makes it more qualified to be an SCP than like half of the Antimemetics Division tales.

I physically cannot bring myself to downvote something of this caliber, and at the same time I don't know if I can upvote something that basically tosses out the format wholesale with no in-universe justification for it. I'll get back to you.







