Neutral Vote via Caveats


19 Jan 2020 01:19






I overall like the way this story is being laid out, but I think the actual structure can be somewhat disparate at times. I will be honest; I didn't like the beginning at first and still struggle to fully parse what the relationship is between the opening and the ending. I almost feel like the opening could be removed entirely so we can get right into it. I find the general worldbuilding in this piece to be excellent otherwise, although I admit I don't like all the reactions- I don't feel like some of them add to the piece. I feel you could cut it down to 1-2 responses per round of emails for sake of brevity.

Also, personally, I don't like the table of contents. I read this whole thing in one go and cannot discern the differences between the parts (and from what I can discern, 9 seems like way too much.)








Living the dream, or dreaming the life?






